_description: ‘The Kings of England’, an expanded and widely variant version of 5731, continuing to 1505 — twenty-two eight-line stanzas (ababbcbc)

BodRawC448.First Lines:
Wyllyam conquerour duke of NormandieConquerd ynglond & began
                    here to regneThe mlxvii yere of cryst trevlieThe englysh men ageyn
                    rebelled but he subdwed to ther peyne…
BodRawC448.Last Lines:
…[ ]at sol pray to god omnipotent[ ] kynge henry our lorde
                    & souerayngne
BodRawC448.Note:
The portion of the poem on f. 182v is in the lower
                    margins.
